s_article_link` | pure staticmethod, zero tests — trailing `-.html` excluded, external/absolute (`://` or leading `/`) excluded, `_`-prefixed author/keyword pages excluded, valid relative `.html` slug accepted |\n| `MadagascarTribune._discover_categories` | untested — regex extraction of `rubrique\\d+` ids, dedup+sort by int, homepage fetch failure → returns `[]` (not raise) |\n| `MadagascarTribune.list_article_urls` | untested — pagination via `debut_articles` offset, redirect canonicalization (`page.url` reassignment), empty-page-break (`new_on_page == 0`), `_max_pages_per_category` cap enforcement, per-page fetch failure breaks category (not whole crawl) |\n| `FreeNews.list_article_urls` | untested — pagination increment, `HTTPError 400` (`rest_post_invalid_page_number`) treated as normal termination vs other HTTP errors re-raised, empty `posts` list breaks, missing `link` key in a post skipped |\n| `Moov.list_article_urls` | untested — BFS frontier expansion, `queued` set dedup, non-`/article/` links filtered, per-page fetch failure during expansion doesn't crash (continues BFS), seed-only failure (home fetch) currently **unguarded** — not caught, would propagate (worth confirming intended behavior) |\n| `PROVIDERS` registry | untested — every entry is instantiable, `source_name` matches its dict key (used to derive state/log/data paths), sitemap-based providers all have `sitemap_url` set except the 3 that override `list_article_urls` |\n\n### 4. `main.py` — CLI entry point\n\n- Untested: `--provider all` expands to every key in `PROVIDERS`; single-provider selection; `argparse` rejects unknown provider (via `choices`); `--limit` default of `10`; `--limit 0` passed through as unlimited; `on_save` print callback format.\n\n### 5. Integration gaps\n\n- No end-to-end test of `crawl()` against a fake `NewsSource` subclass with an in-memory/mock `Fetcher` — this is the most valuable single test to add since it exercises the entire state machine without hitting the network.\n- No test verifies state/log/data files are correctly namespaced per `source_name` and don't collide across providers.\n- No test of `_fetch_xml` + `discover_sitemap_urls` composed together against a mocked `urlopen`.\n\n---\n\n## Test skeletons\n\nTestability note: `STATE_DIR`/`DATA_DIR`/`LOG_DIR` are module-level constants derived from `ROOT_DIR`. Tests need `monkeypatch.setattr(base, \"STATE_DIR\", tmp_path / \"state\")` etc. (and same on the `NewsSource` instance properties, which read the module globals directly) to avoid touching real repo state/data/logs.\n\n```python\n# tests/conftest.py\nimport pytest\nimport base\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef isolated_dirs(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(base, \"STATE_DIR\", tmp_path / \"state\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(base, \"DATA_DIR\", tmp_path / \"data\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(base, \"LOG_DIR\", tmp_path / \"logs\")\n    return tmp_path\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base_dates.py\nimport pytest\nfrom base import parse_french_date, parse_numeric_date\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n    (\"22 juin 2019\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n    (\"octobre 30, 2017\", \"2017-10-30\"),\n    (\"1 février 2020\", \"2020-02-01\"),\n    (\"1 fevrier 2020\", \"2020-02-01\"),  # unaccented variant\n    (\"3 août 2021\", \"2021-08-03\"),\n    (\"Some prefix text 5 mars 2022 suffix\", \"2022-03-05\"),\n])\ndef test_parse_french_date_valid(text, expected):\n    assert parse_french_date(text) == expected\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text\", [\n    \"not a date at all\",\n    \"22 blorptember 2019\",  # unknown month\n    \"\",\n])\ndef test_parse_french_date_invalid(text):\n    assert parse_french_date(text) is None\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n    (\"12/05/2021\", \"2021-05-12\"),\n    (\"12/05/2021 14:30\", \"2021-05-12\"),\n    (\"1/1/2020\", \"2020-01-01\"),\n])\ndef test_parse_numeric_date_valid(text, expected):\n    assert parse_numeric_date(text) == expected\n\n\ndef test_parse_numeric_date_invalid():\n    assert parse_numeric_date(\"no date here\") is None\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base_sitemap.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom base import discover_sitemap_urls, _fetch_xml\nimport gzip\n\n\ndef test_fetch_xml_gzip_sniffed(monkeypatch):\n    body = gzip.compress(b\"<urlset></urlset>\")\n\n    class FakeResp:\n        def read(self):\n            return body\n        def __enter__(self):\n            return self\n        def __exit__(self, *a):\n            return False\n\n    with patch(\"urllib.request.urlopen\", return_value=FakeResp()):\n        assert _fetch_xml(\"http://x/sitemap.xml\") == \"<urlset></urlset>\"\n\n\ndef test_fetch_xml_strips_leading_whitespace():\n    ...  # feed raw bytes with a leading \"\\n\" before \"<?xml\", assert stripped\n\n\ndef test_discover_sitemap_urls_flat_urlset(monkeypatch):\n    xml = \"\"\"<urlset><url><loc>http://a/1</loc></url>\n              <url><loc>http://a/2</loc></url></urlset>\"\"\"\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"base._fetch_xml\", lambda url: xml)\n    assert list(discover_sitemap_urls(\"http://a/sitemap.xml\")) == [\n        \"http://a/1\", \"http://a/2\",\n    ]\n\n\ndef test_discover_sitemap_urls_index_recurses(monkeypatch):\n    index_xml = \"<sitemapindex><sitemap><loc>http://a/sub.xml</loc></sitemap></sitemapindex>\"\n    leaf_xml = \"<urlset><url><loc>http://a/article-1</loc></url></urlset>\"\n    calls = {\"http://a/index.xml\": index_xml, \"http://a/sub.xml\": leaf_xml}\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"base._fetch_xml\", lambda url: calls[url])\n    assert list(discover_sitemap_urls(\"http://a/index.xml\")) == [\"http://a/article-1\"]\n\n\ndef test_discover_sitemap_urls_ignores_nested_image_loc(monkeypatch):\n    xml = \"\"\"<urlset>\n        <url>\n          <loc>http://a/1</loc>\n          <image:image><image:loc>http://a/1.jpg</image:loc></image:image>\n        </url>\n    </urlset>\"\"\"\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"base._fetch_xml\", lambda url: xml)\n    assert list(discover_sitemap_urls(\"http://a/sitemap.xml\")) == [\"http://a/1\"]\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base_state.py\nfrom base import NewsSource\nfrom models import SiteSelectors\n\n\nclass FakeSource(NewsSource):\n    source_name = \"fake\"\n    selectors = SiteSelectors(title=\"h1\", body=\"p\")\n\n\ndef test_load_state_missing_file_returns_default(isolated_dirs):\n    src = FakeSource()\n    assert src._load_state() == {\"seen_urls\": [], \"total_saved\": 0}\n\n\ndef test_save_state_is_atomic_and_roundtrips(isolated_dirs):\n    src = FakeSource()\n    src._save_state({\"seen_urls\": [\"u1\"], \"total_saved\": 1})\n    assert src._load_state() == {\"seen_urls\": [\"u1\"], \"total_saved\": 1}\n    assert not src._state_path.with_suffix(\".json.tmp\").exists()\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base_crawl.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom base import NewsSource\nfrom models import Article, SiteSelectors\n\n\nclass FakeSource(NewsSource):\n    source_name = \"fake\"\n    selectors = SiteSelectors(title=\"h1\", body=\"p\")\n\n    def __init__(self, urls, articles_by_url, fail_on=(), none_on=()):\n        self._urls = urls\n        self._articles_by_url = articles_by_url\n        self._fail_on = set(fail_on)\n        self._none_on = set(none_on)\n\n    def list_article_urls(self):\n        yield from self._urls\n\n    def parse_article(self, url):\n        if url in self._fail_on:\n            raise RuntimeError(\"boom\")\n        if url in self._none_on:\n            return None\n        return self._articles_by_url[url]\n\n\ndef _article(url):\n    return Article(url=url, title=\"t\", body=\"b\", author=None, published_date=None,\n                    category=None, source=\"fake\", scraped_at=\"now\")\n\n\ndef test_crawl_skips_already_seen(isolated_dirs):\n    src = FakeSource([\"u1\", \"u2\"], {\"u1\": _article(\"u1\"), \"u2\": _article(\"u2\")})\n    src._save_state({\"seen_urls\": [\"u1\"], \"total_saved\": 1})\n    saved = src.crawl(limit=10)\n    assert [a.url for a in saved] == [\"u2\"]\n\n\ndef test_crawl_marks_none_article_as_seen_without_saving(isolated_dirs):\n    src = FakeSource([\"u1\"], {}, none_on=[\"u1\"])\n    saved = src.crawl(limit=10)\n    assert saved == []\n    assert \"u1\" in src._load_state()[\"seen_urls\"]\n\n\ndef test_crawl_parse_error_not_marked_seen(isolated_dirs):\n    src = FakeSource([\"u1\"], {}, fail_on=[\"u1\"])\n    saved = src.crawl(limit=10)\n    assert saved == []\n    assert \"u1\" not in src._load_state()[\"seen_urls\"]  # retried next run\n\n\ndef test_crawl_stops_at_limit(isolated_dirs):\n    urls = [\"u1\", \"u2\", \"u3\"]\n    src = FakeSource(urls, {u: _article(u) for u in urls})\n    saved = src.crawl(limit=2)\n    assert len(saved) == 2\n    assert src._load_state()[\"last_stopped_reason\"] == \"limit reached\"\n\n\ndef test_crawl_unlimited_runs_to_exhaustion(isolated_dirs):\n    urls = [\"u1\", \"u2\"]\n    src = FakeSource(urls, {u: _article(u) for u in urls})\n    saved = src.crawl(limit=0)\n    assert len(saved) == 2\n    assert src._load_state()[\"last_stopped_reason\"] == \"exhausted\"\n\n\ndef test_crawl_discovery_error_saved_gracefully(isolated_dirs):\n    class BrokenDiscovery(FakeSource):\n        def list_article_urls(self):\n            yield \"u1\"\n            raise ConnectionError(\"network down\")\n\n    src = BrokenDiscovery([\"u1\"], {\"u1\": _article(\"u1\")})\n    saved = src.crawl(limit=10)  # must not raise\n    assert len(saved) == 1\n    assert \"error: network down\" in src._load_state()[\"last_stopped_reason\"]\n\n\ndef test_crawl_on_save_callback_invoked(isolated_dirs):\n    src = FakeSource([\"u1\"], {\"u1\": _article(\"u1\")})\n    seen = []\n    src.crawl(limit=10, on_save=seen.append)\n    assert len(seen) == 1 and seen[0].url == \"u1\"\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_base_parse_article.py\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock\nfrom base import NewsSource\nfrom models import SiteSelectors\n\n\ndef make_page(title_text=None, body_paras=(), author_text=None,\n              date_text=None, date_attr=None, category_text=None,\n              og_image=None, iframe_src=None, video_src=None, imgs=()):\n    \"\"\"Build a MagicMock standing in for a scrapling page, keyed by CSS selector.\"\"\"\n    ...  # configure page.css(selector).first / iteration per-selector as needed\n\n\ndef test_parse_article_returns_none_without_title():\n    ...\n\n\ndef test_parse_article_reads_date_from_attr_when_configured():\n    ...\n\n\ndef test_parse_article_parses_french_date_text_when_no_attr():\n    ...\n\n\ndef test_parse_article_prefers_iframe_over_video_source():\n    ...\n\n\ndef test_parse_article_falls_back_to_video_source_when_no_iframe():\n    ...\n\n\ndef test_parse_article_skips_about_blank_iframe():\n    ...\n\n\ndef test_extract_images_dedupes_and_prefers_data_src():\n    ...\n\n\ndef test_extract_images_excludes_data_uris():\n    ...\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_providers.py\nimport pytest\nfrom providers import PROVIDERS, MadagascarTribune, FreeNews\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"name,cls\", PROVIDERS.items())\ndef test_provider_source_name_matches_registry_key(name, cls):\n    assert cls().source_name == name\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"href,expected\", [\n    (\"some-article.html\", True),\n    (\"category-.html\", False),\n    (\"http://external.com/x.html\", False),\n    (\"/absolute/path.html\", False),\n    (\"_AuthorName,42_.html\", False),\n    (None, False),\n    (\"no-extension\", False),\n])\ndef test_tribune_is_article_link(href, expected):\n    assert MadagascarTribune._is_article_link(href) is expected\n\n\ndef test_freenews_pagination_stops_on_400(monkeypatch):\n    # mock urllib.request.urlopen: page 1 returns posts, page 2 raises HTTPError(400)\n    ...\n\n\ndef test_freenews_pagination_reraises_other_http_errors(monkeypatch):\n    ...\n\n\ndef test_tribune_discover_categories_handles_fetch_failure(monkeypatch):\n    ...  # Fetcher.get raises -> _discover_categories returns []\n\n\ndef test_moov_bfs_dedupes_queued_urls(monkeypatch):\n    ...\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_main.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport main\n\n\ndef test_all_provider_expands_to_full_registry(monkeypatch):\n    with patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"main.py\", \"all\", \"--limit\", \"1\"]):\n        with patch(\"providers.PROVIDERS\") as mocked:\n            ...  # assert every provider's .crawl() called once\n\n\ndef test_single_provider_only_crawls_that_one(monkeypatch):\n    ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Priority order\n\n1. `NewsSource.crawl` (state machine, resumability, error isolation) — highest risk, no coverage, affects every provider.\n2. `parse_article` + `_extract_images` — most branch-heavy pure-ish logic, easy to unit test with mocked page objects.\n3. `parse_french_date` / `parse_numeric_date` — pure functions, cheap wins, currently zero coverage.\n4. `discover_sitemap_urls` / `_fetch_xml` — network-adjacent but mockable, covers 8 of 11 providers.\n5. Custom provider crawlers (`MadagascarTribune`, `FreeNews`, `Moov`) — bespoke pagination/BFS logic with no shared test path.\n6. `main.py` CLI glue — low complexity, quick smoke tests.\n\nAdd `tests/` (per this repo's own root-file rule: don't drop test files at project root) with `conftest.py` for the `isolated_dirs` fixture, and wire `pytest` into whatever CI/verify flow this repo uses.\n",
