        "title": "tests/test_base_dates.py",
        "content": "import pytest\nfrom base import parse_french_date, parse_numeric_date\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n    (\"22 juin 2019\", \"2019-06-22\"),\n    (\"octobre 30, 2017\", \"2017-10-30\"),\n    (\"1 février 2020\", \"2020-02-01\"),\n    (\"1 fevrier 2020\", \"2020-02-01\"),  # unaccented variant\n    (\"3 août 2021\", \"2021-08-03\"),\n    (\"Some prefix text 5 mars 2022 suffix\", \"2022-03-05\"),\n])\ndef test_parse_french_date_valid(text, expected):\n    assert parse_french_date(text) == expected\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text\", [\n    \"not a date at all\",\n    \"22 blorptember 2019\",  # unknown month\n    \"\",\n])\ndef test_parse_french_date_invalid(text):\n    assert parse_french_date(text) is None\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"text,expected\", [\n    (\"12/05/2021\", \"2021-05-12\"),\n    (\"12/05/2021 14:30\", \"2021-05-12\"),\n    (\"1/1/2020\", \"2020-01-01\"),\n])\ndef test_parse_numeric_date_valid(text, expected):\n    assert parse_numeric_date(text) == expected\n\n\ndef test_parse_numeric_date_invalid():\n    assert parse_numeric_date(\"no date here\") is None\n```\n\n```python\n",
